title.narrative: DOF has adapted and implemented legal and regulatory frameworks on Union and local level to provide for inshore fisheries co-management and combating IUU fishing on Union Level
Marine fisheries law and regulatory frameworks amended to include inshore fisheries and MCS unit is established

actual.value: A revised draft of Marine Fisheries Law Providing detailed comments for each single revision was prepared and fed into the Parliament deliberation process

actual.value: Community informer network were formed. DoF and Marine Police received training on MCS. Inshore inspection was about to start with the launching of the 2 inspection vessels. Activities interrupted due to political situation

target.value: Fisheries law approved and MCS unit operational

actual.value: SCF met with four Agriculture. Livestock and Fisheries Development COmmittee members. The members showed keen interest in recommendtions regarding MCS and VMS and DOF agreed to procure the planned Legal assistance to provide guidance for the next draft of the new Marine Fisheries Law. A Task Force unit for MCS and Co-management has been established in 2018. in preparation for the establishment of an MCS Division and a permanent institutional arrangement for Co-management (a Co-Management Unit).

title.narrative: Community livelihoods improved based on sustainable resource use and in-creased value added of landings
Community awareness increased on food safety, hygiene and quality and post-harvest losses decreased on board fishing vessels and on land resulting in higher prices

target.value: 8 DOF State/Regional food safety inspectors are trainined as trainer in Sanitary and Pyto Sanitary requirements and hygienic aspects. And community members trained in all 8 pilot communities in food safety and hygiene. quality and environmental awareness

actual.value: 25 district level food safety inspectors received trainings Community members trained in 7 pilot projects

target.value: Qualitative assessment of catch handling on board vessels and on land show reduced post-harvest losses. Higher prices when trading with local trader's due to improved quality of products. qualitative assess improved state of food safety. hygiene. environmental awareness

actual.value: Food safety conservation training and awareness raising finalized. Data collection on use f ice box and quality assessment of catch handling and post-harvest loss underway

target.value: Qualitative assessment of catch handling on board vessels and on land show reduced post-harvest losses. Higher prices when trading with local trader's due to improved quality of products. qualitative assess improved state of food safety. hygiene. environmental awareness

actual.value: Turn over from coastal fisheries increased by at least 5% in the pilot areas as a result of increased compliance with fishing regulations (less destructive fishing methods, selective gear applied, which will lead to larger fish sizes and eventually larger quantities) and decreased post-harvest losses (larger and fresher fish of higher value, losses reduced to 5% at sea and to 1% on land)
